from every boat, seemed only intent on annihilating each separate plank of 
which those boats were made. But skilfully manœuvred, incessantly wheeling 
like trained chargers in the field; the boats for a while eluded him; though, 
at times, but by a plank’s breadth; while all the time, Ahab’s unearthly 
slogan tore every other cry but his to shreds.
